WEBVTT

00:00:00.200 --> 00:00:03.436
An Employee is eligible for a career ladder promotion when he

00:00:03.503 --> 00:00:06.940
or she completes at least one year in the current grade;

00:00:07.006 --> 00:00:09.676
demonstrates the ability to perform the higher-grade level

00:00:09.743 --> 00:00:14.414
duties; and has an acceptable current written performance appraisal.

00:00:14.481 --> 00:00:17.517
In order to be acceptable, the Employee's current rating of

00:00:17.584 --> 00:00:20.987
record must be Fully Successful or higher.

00:00:21.054 --> 00:00:24.657
Also, no critical performance element can be rated below Fully

00:00:24.724 --> 00:00:28.328
Successful if it is also a critical element at the next

00:00:28.395 --> 00:00:30.930
higher level of the career ladder.

00:00:30.997 --> 00:00:34.067
Two more conditions depend on the Department.

00:00:34.134 --> 00:00:37.337
The Department must have sufficient work and sufficient

00:00:37.404 --> 00:00:40.306
funds for the higher grade-level position.


